{
  "video_id": "qQ-PUXPVlos",
  "title": "How we need to remake the internet | Jaron Lanier",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12944.0,
      "end_time": 16953.0,
      "text": "Back in the 1980s, actually, I gave my first talk at TED,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16977.0,
      "end_time": 21239.0,
      "text": "and I brought some of the very, very first public demonstrations"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 21263.0,
      "end_time": 25497.0,
      "text": "of virtual reality ever to the TED stage."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 26375.0,
      "end_time": 33242.0,
      "text": "And at that time, we knew that we were facing a knife-edge future"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 33266.0,
      "end_time": 38467.0,
      "text": "where the technology we needed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 38491.0,
      "end_time": 40342.0,
      "text": "the technology we loved,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 40366.0,
      "end_time": 42413.0,
      "text": "could also be our undoing."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 43266.0,
      "end_time": 47357.0,
      "text": "We knew that if we thought of our technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 47381.0,
      "end_time": 50635.0,
      "text": "as a means to ever more power,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 50659.0,
      "end_time": 54366.0,
      "text": "if it was just a power trip, we&#39;d eventually destroy ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 54390.0,
      "end_time": 55571.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s what happens"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 55595.0,
      "end_time": 58382.0,
      "text": "when you&#39;re on a power trip and nothing else."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 59509.0,
      "end_time": 62898.0,
      "text": "So the idealism"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 62922.0,
      "end_time": 67731.0,
      "text": "of digital culture back then"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 67755.0,
      "end_time": 72494.0,
      "text": "was all about starting with that recognition of the possible darkness"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 72518.0,
      "end_time": 75868.0,
      "text": "and trying to imagine a way to transcend it"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 75892.0,
      "end_time": 78470.0,
      "text": "with beauty and creativity."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 79330.0,
      "end_time": 85540.0,
      "text": "I always used to end my early TED Talks with a rather horrifying line, which is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 86478.0,
      "end_time": 90344.0,
      "text": "\"We have a challenge."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 90368.0,
      "end_time": 94392.0,
      "text": "We have to create a culture around technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 94416.0,
      "end_time": 98384.0,
      "text": "that is so beautiful, so meaningful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 98408.0,
      "end_time": 100949.0,
      "text": "so deep, so endlessly creative,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 100973.0,
      "end_time": 103989.0,
      "text": "so filled with infinite potential"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 104130.0,
      "end_time": 107266.0,
      "text": "that it draws us away from committing mass suicide.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 108519.0,
      "end_time": 114107.0,
      "text": "So we talked about extinction as being one and the same"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 114131.0,
      "end_time": 118961.0,
      "text": "as the need to create an alluring, infinitely creative future."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 119639.0,
      "end_time": 125210.0,
      "text": "And I still believe that that alternative of creativity"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 125450.0,
      "end_time": 127190.0,
      "text": "as an alternative to death"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 127430.0,
      "end_time": 129120.0,
      "text": "is very real and true,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 129360.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131190.0,
      "text": "maybe the most true thing there is."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 131870.0,
      "end_time": 133965.0,
      "text": "In the case of virtual reality --"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 133989.0,
      "end_time": 136271.0,
      "text": "well, the way I used to talk about it"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 136295.0,
      "end_time": 138929.0,
      "text": "is that it would be something like"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 138954.0,
      "end_time": 141804.0,
      "text": "what happened when people discovered language."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 141828.0,
      "end_time": 146503.0,
      "text": "With language came new adventures, new depth, new meaning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 146527.0,
      "end_time": 148607.0,
      "text": "new ways to connect, new ways to coordinate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 148631.0,
      "end_time": 152665.0,
      "text": "new ways to imagine, new ways to raise children,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 152689.0,
      "end_time": 156951.0,
      "text": "and I imagined, with virtual reality, we&#39;d have this new thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 156975.0,
      "end_time": 158567.0,
      "text": "that would be like a conversation"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 158592.0,
      "end_time": 161936.0,
      "text": "but also like waking-state intentional dreaming."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 161960.0,
      "end_time": 164613.0,
      "text": "We called it post-symbolic communication,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 164637.0,
      "end_time": 168995.0,
      "text": "because it would be like just directly making the thing you experienced"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 169190.0,
      "end_time": 172638.0,
      "text": "instead of indirectly making symbols to refer to things."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 173466.0,
      "end_time": 177804.0,
      "text": "It was a beautiful vision, and it&#39;s one I still believe in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 177828.0,
      "end_time": 181430.0,
      "text": "and yet, haunting that beautiful vision"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 181670.0,
      "end_time": 184217.0,
      "text": "was the dark side of how it could also turn out."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 184241.0,
      "end_time": 189289.0,
      "text": "And I suppose I could mention"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 189313.0,
      "end_time": 192376.0,
      "text": "from one of the very earliest computer scientists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 192401.0,
      "end_time": 194536.0,
      "text": "whose name was Norbert Wiener,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 194560.0,
      "end_time": 198314.0,
      "text": "and he wrote a book back in the &#39;50s, from before I was even born,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 198338.0,
      "end_time": 200995.0,
      "text": "called \"The Human Use of Human Beings.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 201779.0,
      "end_time": 205951.0,
      "text": "And in the book, he described the potential"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 205975.0,
      "end_time": 212156.0,
      "text": "to create a computer system that would be gathering data from people"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 212180.0,
      "end_time": 215752.0,
      "text": "and providing feedback to those people in real time"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 215776.0,
      "end_time": 220911.0,
      "text": "in order to put them kind of partially, statistically, in a Skinner box,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 220935.0,
      "end_time": 223379.0,
      "text": "in a behaviorist system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 223403.0,
      "end_time": 225904.0,
      "text": "and he has this amazing line where he says,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 225928.0,
      "end_time": 228666.0,
      "text": "one could imagine, as a thought experiment --"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 228690.0,
      "end_time": 231151.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;m paraphrasing, this isn&#39;t a quote --"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 231175.0,
      "end_time": 234255.0,
      "text": "one could imagine a global computer system"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 234279.0,
      "end_time": 237121.0,
      "text": "where everybody has devices on them all the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 237145.0,
      "end_time": 240417.0,
      "text": "and the devices are giving them feedback based on what they did,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 240441.0,
      "end_time": 242316.0,
      "text": "and the whole population"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 242340.0,
      "end_time": 245916.0,
      "text": "is subject to a degree of behavior modification."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 245940.0,
      "end_time": 249486.0,
      "text": "And such a society would be insane,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 249510.0,
      "end_time": 252607.0,
      "text": "could not survive, could not face its problems."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 252631.0,
      "end_time": 255252.0,
      "text": "And then he says, but this is only a thought experiment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 255276.0,
      "end_time": 258696.0,
      "text": "and such a future is technologically infeasible."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 258720.00000000003,
      "end_time": 259812.00000000003,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 259836.0,
      "end_time": 262838.0,
      "text": "And yet, of course, it&#39;s what we have created,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 262862.0,
      "end_time": 266139.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s what we must undo if we are to survive."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 267457.0,
      "end_time": 268608.0,
      "text": "So --"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 268632.0,
      "end_time": 272172.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 272631.0,
      "end_time": 278607.0,
      "text": "I believe that we made a very particular mistake,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 278632.0,
      "end_time": 280866.0,
      "text": "and it happened early on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 280890.0,
      "end_time": 282964.0,
      "text": "and by understanding the mistake we made,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 282988.0,
      "end_time": 284847.0,
      "text": "we can undo it."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 284871.0,
      "end_time": 287430.0,
      "text": "It happened in the &#39;90s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 287454.0,
      "end_time": 290196.0,
      "text": "and going into the turn of the century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 290220.0,
      "end_time": 291608.0,
      "text": "and here&#39;s what happened."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 293200.0,
      "end_time": 294574.0,
      "text": "Early digital culture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 294598.0,
      "end_time": 299570.0,
      "text": "and indeed, digital culture to this day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 299594.0,
      "end_time": 305903.0,
      "text": "had a sense of, I would say, lefty, socialist mission about it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 305927.0,
      "end_time": 308870.0,
      "text": "that unlike other things that have been done,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 308111.0,
      "end_time": 309545.0,
      "text": "like the invention of books,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 309569.0,
      "end_time": 312982.0,
      "text": "everything on the internet must be purely public,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 313600.0,
      "end_time": 315330.0,
      "text": "must be available for free,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 315355.0,
      "end_time": 318743.0,
      "text": "because if even one person cannot afford it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 318767.0,
      "end_time": 321339.0,
      "text": "then that would create this terrible inequity."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 321912.0,
      "end_time": 324436.0,
      "text": "Now of course, there&#39;s other ways to deal with that."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 324460.0,
      "end_time": 327476.0,
      "text": "If books cost money, you can have public libraries."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 327500.0,
      "end_time": 328674.0,
      "text": "And so forth."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 328698.0,
      "end_time": 331316.0,
      "text": "But we were thinking, no, no, no, this is an exception."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 331340.0,
      "end_time": 335945.0,
      "text": "This must be pure public commons, that&#39;s what we want."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 335969.0,
      "end_time": 338603.0,
      "text": "And so that spirit lives on."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 338627.0,
      "end_time": 342342.0,
      "text": "You can experience it in designs like the Wikipedia, for instance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 342366.0,
      "end_time": 343707.0,
      "text": "many others."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 343731.0,
      "end_time": 345605.0,
      "text": "But at the same time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 345629.0,
      "end_time": 348217.0,
      "text": "we also believed, with equal fervor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 348241.0,
      "end_time": 352178.0,
      "text": "in this other thing that was completely incompatible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 352202.0,
      "end_time": 355829.0,
      "text": "which is we loved our tech entrepreneurs."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 355853.0,
      "end_time": 359592.0,
      "text": "We loved Steve Jobs; we loved this Nietzschean myth"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 359616.0,
      "end_time": 363840.0,
      "text": "of the techie who could dent the universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 363108.0,
      "end_time": 364426.0,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 364450.0,
      "end_time": 370298.0,
      "text": "And that mythical power still has a hold on us, as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 370322.0,
      "end_time": 374781.0,
      "text": "So you have these two different passions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 374805.0,
      "end_time": 376742.0,
      "text": "for making everything free"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 376766.0,
      "end_time": 381932.0,
      "text": "and for the almost supernatural power of the tech entrepreneur."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 381956.0,
      "end_time": 386308.0,
      "text": "How do you celebrate entrepreneurship when everything&#39;s free?"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 386332.0,
      "end_time": 389457.0,
      "text": "Well, there was only one solution back then,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 389481.0,
      "end_time": 391568.0,
      "text": "which was the advertising model."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 391592.0,
      "end_time": 395594.0,
      "text": "And so therefore, Google was born free, with ads,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 395619.0,
      "end_time": 399301.0,
      "text": "Facebook was born free, with ads."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 399325.0,
      "end_time": 403190.0,
      "text": "Now in the beginning, it was cute,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 403214.0,
      "end_time": 405174.0,
      "text": "like with the very earliest Google."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 405198.0,
      "end_time": 406484.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 406508.0,
      "end_time": 409405.0,
      "text": "The ads really were kind of ads."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 409429.0,
      "end_time": 411914.0,
      "text": "They would be, like, your local dentist or something."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 411938.0,
      "end_time": 413858.0,
      "text": "But there&#39;s thing called Moore&#39;s law"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 413882.0,
      "end_time": 417240.0,
      "text": "that makes the computers more and more efficient and cheaper."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 417480.0,
      "end_time": 418906.0,
      "text": "Their algorithms get better."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 418930.0,
      "end_time": 421526.0,
      "text": "We actually have universities where people study them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 421550.0,
      "end_time": 423178.0,
      "text": "and they get better and better."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 423202.0,
      "end_time": 427654.0,
      "text": "And the customers and other entities who use these systems"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 427678.0,
      "end_time": 431805.0,
      "text": "just got more and more experienced and got cleverer and cleverer."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 431829.0,
      "end_time": 434226.0,
      "text": "And what started out as advertising"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 434250.0,
      "end_time": 436727.0,
      "text": "really can&#39;t be called advertising anymore."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 436751.0,
      "end_time": 439662.0,
      "text": "It turned into behavior modification,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 439687.0,
      "end_time": 444180.0,
      "text": "just as Norbert Wiener had worried it might."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 444204.0,
      "end_time": 448824.0,
      "text": "And so I can&#39;t call these things social networks anymore."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 448848.0,
      "end_time": 452662.0,
      "text": "I call them behavior modification empires."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 452686.0,
      "end_time": 454921.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 454945.0,
      "end_time": 459159.0,
      "text": "And I refuse to vilify the individuals."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 459183.0,
      "end_time": 461454.0,
      "text": "I have dear friends at these companies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 461478.0,
      "end_time": 466238.0,
      "text": "sold a company to Google, even though I think it&#39;s one of these empires."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 466262.0,
      "end_time": 471322.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t think this is a matter of bad people who&#39;ve done a bad thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 471346.0,
      "end_time": 475922.0,
      "text": "I think this is a matter of a globally tragic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 475946.0,
      "end_time": 480518.0,
      "text": "astoundingly ridiculous mistake,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 480542.0,
      "end_time": 484671.0,
      "text": "rather than a wave of evil."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 484695.0,
      "end_time": 487377.0,
      "text": "Let me give you just another layer of detail"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 487401.0,
      "end_time": 490504.0,
      "text": "into how this particular mistake functions."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 491337.0,
      "end_time": 494440.0,
      "text": "So with behaviorism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 494680.0,
      "end_time": 499132.0,
      "text": "you give the creature, whether it&#39;s a rat or a dog or a person,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 499156.0,
      "end_time": 501996.0,
      "text": "little treats and sometimes little punishments"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 502200.0,
      "end_time": 503837.0,
      "text": "as feedback to what they do."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 504710.0,
      "end_time": 510621.0,
      "text": "So if you have an animal in a cage, it might be candy and electric shocks."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 510646.0,
      "end_time": 513169.0,
      "text": "But if you have a smartphone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 513193.0,
      "end_time": 520120.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s not those things, it&#39;s symbolic punishment and reward."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 520144.0,
      "end_time": 522587.0,
      "text": "Pavlov, one of the early behaviorists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 522611.0,
      "end_time": 525563.0,
      "text": "demonstrated the famous principle."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 525587.0,
      "end_time": 529548.0,
      "text": "You could train a dog to salivate just with the bell, just with the symbol."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 529572.0,
      "end_time": 531158.0,
      "text": "So on social networks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 531182.0,
      "end_time": 536262.0,
      "text": "social punishment and social reward function as the punishment and reward."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 536286.0,
      "end_time": 538363.0,
      "text": "And we all know the feeling of these things."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 538387.0,
      "end_time": 539838.0,
      "text": "You get this little thrill --"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 539862.0,
      "end_time": 542212.0,
      "text": "\"Somebody liked my stuff and it&#39;s being repeated.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 542236.0,
      "end_time": 544569.0,
      "text": "Or the punishment: \"Oh my God, they don&#39;t like me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 544594.0,
      "end_time": 546833.0,
      "text": "maybe somebody else is more popular, oh my God.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 546857.0,
      "end_time": 549830.0,
      "text": "So you have those two very common feelings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 549107.0,
      "end_time": 552670.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;re doled out in such a way that you get caught in this loop."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 552695.0,
      "end_time": 556790.0,
      "text": "As has been publicly acknowledged by many of the founders of the system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 556814.0,
      "end_time": 559155.0,
      "text": "everybody knew this is what was going on."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 559871.0,
      "end_time": 561490.0,
      "text": "But here&#39;s the thing:"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 561514.0,
      "end_time": 566808.0,
      "text": "traditionally, in the academic study of the methods of behaviorism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 566832.0,
      "end_time": 572268.0,
      "text": "there have been comparisons of positive and negative stimuli."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 572292.0,
      "end_time": 574656.0,
      "text": "In this setting, a commercial setting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 574680.0,
      "end_time": 576276.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s a new kind of difference"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 576300.0,
      "end_time": 579690.0,
      "text": "that has kind of evaded the academic world for a while,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 579930.0,
      "end_time": 583141.0,
      "text": "and that difference is that whether positive stimuli"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 583165.0,
      "end_time": 586473.0,
      "text": "are more effective than negative ones in different circumstances,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 586498.0,
      "end_time": 588602.0,
      "text": "the negative ones are cheaper."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 588626.0,
      "end_time": 590682.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re the bargain stimuli."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 590706.0,
      "end_time": 596409.0,
      "text": "So what I mean by that is it&#39;s much easier"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 596433.0,
      "end_time": 599549.0,
      "text": "to lose trust than to build trust."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 599573.0,
      "end_time": 602745.0,
      "text": "It takes a long time to build love."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 602769.0,
      "end_time": 605375.0,
      "text": "It takes a short time to ruin love."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 605399.0,
      "end_time": 609987.0,
      "text": "Now the customers of these behavior modification empires"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 610110.0,
      "end_time": 611434.0,
      "text": "are on a very fast loop."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 611458.0,
      "end_time": 613502.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re almost like high-frequency traders."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 613527.0,
      "end_time": 615551.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re getting feedbacks from their spends"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 615575.0,
      "end_time": 618377.0,
      "text": "or whatever their activities are if they&#39;re not spending,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 618401.0,
      "end_time": 621670.0,
      "text": "and they see what&#39;s working, and then they do more of that."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 621695.0,
      "end_time": 623735.0,
      "text": "And so they&#39;re getting the quick feedback,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 623759.0,
      "end_time": 626799.0,
      "text": "which means they&#39;re responding more to the negative emotions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 626823.0,
      "end_time": 630760.0,
      "text": "because those are the ones that rise faster, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 630784.0,
      "end_time": 634332.0,
      "text": "And so therefore, even well-intentioned players"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 634356.0,
      "end_time": 637221.0,
      "text": "who think all they&#39;re doing is advertising toothpaste"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 637245.0,
      "end_time": 640276.0,
      "text": "end up advancing the cause of the negative people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 640300.0,
      "end_time": 642633.0,
      "text": "the negative emotions, the cranks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 642658.0,
      "end_time": 644102.0,
      "text": "the paranoids,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 644126.0,
      "end_time": 647206.0,
      "text": "the cynics, the nihilists."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 647230.0,
      "end_time": 650723.0,
      "text": "Those are the ones who get amplified by the system."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 650747.0,
      "end_time": 656397.0,
      "text": "And you can&#39;t pay one of these companies to make the world suddenly nice"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 656422.0,
      "end_time": 657573.0,
      "text": "and improve democracy"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 657597.0,
      "end_time": 661438.0,
      "text": "nearly as easily as you can pay to ruin those things."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 661462.0,
      "end_time": 665181.0,
      "text": "And so this is the dilemma we&#39;ve gotten ourselves into."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 665856.0,
      "end_time": 671880.0,
      "text": "The alternative is to turn back the clock, with great difficulty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 671112.0,
      "end_time": 673953.0,
      "text": "and remake that decision."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 673977.0,
      "end_time": 678150.0,
      "text": "Remaking it would mean two things."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 678390.0,
      "end_time": 681967.0,
      "text": "It would mean first that many people, those who could afford to,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 681991.0,
      "end_time": 684198.0,
      "text": "would actually pay for these things."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 684222.0,
      "end_time": 688629.0,
      "text": "You&#39;d pay for search, you&#39;d pay for social networking."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 688653.0,
      "end_time": 692114.0,
      "text": "How would you pay? Maybe with a subscription fee,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 692138.0,
      "end_time": 694876.0,
      "text": "maybe with micro-payments as you use them."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 694900.0,
      "end_time": 696702.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a lot of options."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 696726.0,
      "end_time": 699123.0,
      "text": "If some of you are recoiling, and you&#39;re thinking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 699147.0,
      "end_time": 701513.0,
      "text": "\"Oh my God, I would never pay for these things."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 701537.0,
      "end_time": 703632.0,
      "text": "How could you ever get anyone to pay?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 703656.0,
      "end_time": 706895.0,
      "text": "I want to remind you of something that just happened."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 706919.0,
      "end_time": 708973.0,
      "text": "Around this same time"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 708997.0,
      "end_time": 714704.0,
      "text": "that companies like Google and Facebook were formulating their free idea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 714728.0,
      "end_time": 719232.0,
      "text": "a lot of cyber culture also believed that in the future,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 719256.0,
      "end_time": 722278.0,
      "text": "televisions and movies would be created in the same way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 722302.0,
      "end_time": 724570.0,
      "text": "kind of like the Wikipedia."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 724456.0,
      "end_time": 729520.0,
      "text": "But then, companies like Netflix, Amazon, HBO,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 729544.0,
      "end_time": 733283.0,
      "text": "said, \"Actually, you know, subscribe. We&#39;ll give you give you great TV.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 733307.0,
      "end_time": 734680.0,
      "text": "And it worked!"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 734704.0,
      "end_time": 738578.0,
      "text": "We now are in this period called \"peak TV,\" right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 738602.0,
      "end_time": 742800.0,
      "text": "So sometimes when you pay for stuff, things get better."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 742824.0,
      "end_time": 745109.0,
      "text": "We can imagine a hypothetical --"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 745134.0,
      "end_time": 749805.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 749829.0,
      "end_time": 753488.0,
      "text": "We can imagine a hypothetical world of \"peak social media.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 753512.0,
      "end_time": 754861.0,
      "text": "What would that be like?"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 754885.0,
      "end_time": 757655.0,
      "text": "It would mean when you get on, you can get really useful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 757679.0,
      "end_time": 760774.0,
      "text": "authoritative medical advice instead of cranks."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 761143.0,
      "end_time": 764453.0,
      "text": "It could mean when you want to get factual information,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 764477.0,
      "end_time": 767731.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s not a bunch of weird, paranoid conspiracy theories."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 767755.0,
      "end_time": 771990.0,
      "text": "We can imagine this wonderful other possibility."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 772140.0,
      "end_time": 773275.0,
      "text": "Ah."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 773299.0,
      "end_time": 775429.0,
      "text": "I dream of it. I believe it&#39;s possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 775453.0,
      "end_time": 778755.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m certain it&#39;s possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 778779.0,
      "end_time": 783526.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;m certain that the companies, the Googles and the Facebooks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 783550.0,
      "end_time": 785862.0,
      "text": "would actually do better in this world."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 785886.0,
      "end_time": 789520.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t believe we need to punish Silicon Valley."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 789760.0,
      "end_time": 791329.0,
      "text": "We just need to remake the decision."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 792702.0,
      "end_time": 794584.0,
      "text": "Of the big tech companies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 794608.0,
      "end_time": 800170.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s really only two that depend on behavior modification and spying"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 800195.0,
      "end_time": 801452.0,
      "text": "as their business plan."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 801476.0,
      "end_time": 803235.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s Google and Facebook."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 803259.0,
      "end_time": 804569.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 804593.0,
      "end_time": 806284.0,
      "text": "And I love you guys."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 806308.0,
      "end_time": 809290.0,
      "text": "Really, I do. Like, the people are fantastic."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 810371.0,
      "end_time": 813553.0,
      "text": "I want to point out, if I may,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 813577.0,
      "end_time": 814728.0,
      "text": "if you look at Google,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 814752.0,
      "end_time": 819839.0,
      "text": "they can propagate cost centers endlessly with all of these companies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 819863.0,
      "end_time": 821911.0,
      "text": "but they cannot propagate profit centers."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 821935.0,
      "end_time": 825116.0,
      "text": "They cannot diversify, because they&#39;re hooked."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 825140.0,
      "end_time": 827766.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re hooked on this model, just like their own users."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 827791.0,
      "end_time": 830890.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re in the same trap as their users,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 830113.0,
      "end_time": 832617.0,
      "text": "and you can&#39;t run a big corporation that way."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 832641.0,
      "end_time": 836243.0,
      "text": "So this is ultimately totally in the benefit of the shareholders"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 836268.0,
      "end_time": 838713.0,
      "text": "and other stakeholders of these companies."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 838737.0,
      "end_time": 841870.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a win-win solution."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 841111.0,
      "end_time": 843626.0,
      "text": "It&#39;ll just take some time to figure it out."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 843650.0,
      "end_time": 845911.0,
      "text": "A lot of details to work out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 845936.0,
      "end_time": 847766.0,
      "text": "totally doable."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 847790.0,
      "end_time": 850204.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 850229.0,
      "end_time": 854630.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t believe our species can survive unless we fix this."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 854870.0,
      "end_time": 856377.0,
      "text": "We cannot have a society"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 856401.0,
      "end_time": 859362.0,
      "text": "in which, if two people wish to communicate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 859386.0,
      "end_time": 862826.0,
      "text": "the only way that can happen is if it&#39;s financed by a third person"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 862850.0,
      "end_time": 865196.0,
      "text": "who wishes to manipulate them."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 865220.0,
      "end_time": 871458.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 875770.0,
      "end_time": 876228.0,
      "text": "(Applause ends)"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 876942.0,
      "end_time": 879887.0,
      "text": "In the meantime, if the companies won&#39;t change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 879911.0,
      "end_time": 881577.0,
      "text": "delete your accounts, OK?"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 881601.0,
      "end_time": 882870.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 882894.0,
      "end_time": 883940.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
